    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's what I've researched and planned — **4 file changes, 2 new + 2 edits**:\n\n---\n\n### New Files\n\n**`ui/stepper.tsx`** — The component, following `carousel.tsx`'s custom context pattern (no Radix UI needed). Uses **dual context**:\n- `StepperContext` — root level, shares `activeStep` + `orientation` with all descendants\n- `StepperItemContext` — per-item level, shares `step` + computed `state` (`\"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\"`) with `StepperTrigger` and `StepperSeparator`\n\nUses `cva` for `StepperTrigger` visual states: filled primary circle (completed), outlined ring (active), muted ring (pending).\n\n7 named exports: `Stepper`, `StepperItem`, `StepperTrigger`, `StepperTitle`, `StepperDescription`, `StepperSeparator`, `StepperContent`.\n\n`StepperSeparator` reads parent item's `state` from context and turns `bg-primary` when `\"completed\"`. `StepperContent` renders `null` unless `step === activeStep`.\n\n**`examples/stepper-demo.tsx`** — A 3-step interactive demo (Account → Profile → Complete) with `React.useState` for `activeStep`, content panels that swap per step, and Previous/Next navigation buttons.\n\n---\n\n### Registry Edits\n\n- **`ui/_registry.ts`**: Insert `stepper` entry (with `\"class-variance-authority\"` as npm dependency) alphabetically between existing `spinner` and `switch` entries (after line 563)\n- **`examples/_registry.ts`**: Insert `stepper-demo` entry (with `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\"]`) between `spinner-item` and `switch-demo` entries (after line 2124)",
